# Documentation Sync

- Separate implemented facts from future plans and unresolved decisions.
- When describing architecture, explicitly state whether it is current code, target design, or a phased recommendation.
- If code and docs disagree, treat the codebase as the source of truth and document the gap clearly.
- Keep project memory focused on durable facts, constraints, and staged decisions.
- Put longer critiques, trade-offs, and design recommendations in dedicated review or architecture docs.
